    <note>Wei Yunzhi [22271] See documentation for grandson, Xiang [22273]. Yunzhi held a post in Xiangyang at end of Tang and, when stranded, settled his family there. XTS, 74A.2b indicates the Xiangyang post, which suggests that the compilers of these genological tables had access to the jiapu of this lineage. According to Zhang(1) Fangping's [217] funerary inscription for descendant, Bufa [22275] (q.v.), Yunzhi moved from Songzhou, Songcheng (moder Shangqiu) county and Yunzhi's cousin, the Tang Zaixiang, Baocheng [22268], is still listed as a Jingzhao resident, I am assuming that Yunzhi's grandfather, Fangxian [22269], made the move to Songzhou.</note>
